      },
      {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13071386/comment/16513114",
        "id": "16513114",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rkanter",
          "name": "rkanter",
          "key": "rkanter",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Robert Kanter",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "I was initially thinking we would want the expiration dates on the child certificates because they should eventually expire for safety, but given that the CN is the AppID and not a host, you'd get browser warnings if someone were to try to reuse the cert elsewhere anyway.  So now I'm thinking that there's no real advantage to worrying about the child cert expiration and we could set it to +10 years or something.  That would also remove the complication about long-running AMs.  Alternatively, instead of setting a long expiration, we could also set a really short one and have the RM ignore the expiration on child certs - that might be safer from an \"outside-the-RM\" perspective.",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rkanter",
          "name": "rkanter",
          "key": "rkanter",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Robert Kanter",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "created": "2018-06-14T23:11:55.729+0000",
        "updated": "2018-06-14T23:12:11.119+0000"
      },
